    {
      "name": "rounding_tie",
      "note": "Coincident-node merge rounding (law 0.2): a near-coincident node pair (e at (6,6) / e2 at (6.0000005,6.0000005)) straddling a 1e-6 half-cell. e2.coord/1e-6 == 6000000.5 is an EXACT half on an EVEN integer, so Python round() (half-to-EVEN) and JS Math.round (half-UP) DIVERGE. Python planar_faces MUST round HALF-UP (math.floor(v+0.5)) to match Math.round: under half-up the two squares stay distinct -> these zone_ids; under the buggy half-even merge e2 would collapse onto e and the second face would become e|p|q|r -> a different SET across languages. Kept in tie_cases (not cases) because the frontend cityFaces.test.ts hardcodes a 'carries the 3 generator cases' assertion on fixture.cases; an orchestrator may add a TS assertion that iterates tie_cases.",
